headline: DXCM Q1 Earnings Call: Coverage Expansion and Product Pipeline Shape 2025 Outlook
summary: Medical device company DexCom (NASDAQ:DXCM) beat Wall Street’s revenue expectations in Q1 CY2025, with sales up 12.5% year on year to $1.04 billion. The company expects the full year’s revenue to be around $4.6 billion, close to analysts’ estimates. Its non-GAAP profit of $0.32 per share was in line with analysts’ consensus estimates.
